ENTRY            F0587   20251215   20260305   20260305       F105
SUBENT        F0587001   20251215   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                 12         25
TITLE      Parameterization of nuclear reactions cross section
           using R-matrix theory.
AUTHOR     (E.Berthoumieux,B.Berthier,C.Moreau,J.P.Gallien,
           A.C.Raoux)
INSTITUTE  (2FR SAC)
REFERENCE  (J,NIM/B,136-138,55,1998)
FACILITY   (VDG,2FR SAC)
SAMPLE     The target consists of a 8 ug/cm2 SiO2 layer
           evaporated onto a 98 nm C backing.
ANALYSIS   Assuming that the alpha scattering by Si is Rutherford
           up to 3.8 MeV, the absolute cross section was deduced
           from the ratio of the oxygen and the silicon peak
           areas. The calibration was made by adjusting current
           data to Leavitt et al. (see REL-REF) measurements at
           the 3032 keV resonance energy.
CORRECTION The experimental results were corrected on a Si
           and O migration into the C backing.
REL-REF    (N,C0091002,J.A.Leavitt+,J,NIM/B,44,260,1990)
METHOD     (LRASY)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-1) Relative error
HISTORY    (20031023C)
           (20251215A) SD: Corrections in all Subents.
           The digitized data were replaced with tabulated data
           received from Eric Berthoumieux on 27 Jan. 2026
           DATA-ERR -> ERR-1. MONITOR -> ANALYSIS.
ENDBIB              25
COMMON               2          3
ANG-ERR    ERR-1
ADEG       PER-CENT
        0.5         5.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           32
SUBENT        F0587002   20251215   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                  4          7
REACTION   (8-O-16(A,EL)8-O-16,,DA)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-S) Statistical error
STATUS     (TABLE,,E.Berthoumieux+,J,NIM/B,136-138,55,1998) part
           of data presented on Fig.2
HISTORY    (20251215A) SD: BIB updated. DATA-ERR1 -> ERR-S.
           MONIT-REF deleted. The digitized data were replaced
           with tabulated data.
ENDBIB               7
NOCOMMON             0          0
